added.title: Gwen Scary, Gwen Lost
added.description: When Chef discovers his spooky Halloween pranks have never scared the kids he's devastated. Determined to get them this year, he agrees to hand over full control of his pranking to Gwen. Her plan turns out far spookier then Chef ever hoped.

added.title: Mad Math: Taffy Road
added.description: After Courtney refuses to share her taffy winnings from a calculus for candy competition, she's transported to the desolate future where she learns that greed is not without consequence.

added.title: Bearly Edible
added.description: After eating the snacks meant for everyone and replacing them with disgusting low budget cookies from Barfvomita, Owen is full of guilt (and cookies) and tries to make things right.

added.title: Ghoul Spirit
added.description: Gwen rejects the friendship of a friendly ghost.

added.title: Duncan Carving
added.description: Duncan takes advantage of a questionable Halloween legend to steal candy from his classmates.

added.title: The Monsters in Your Head
added.description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

added.title: Beware the Scare-Crow
added.description: During a visit to the farm of Penny Bennyson's grandfather, Team Tennyson is constantly haunted by a Scare-Crow that's come to life, but when Ben discovers that Aristocrow is behind it all, our hero must defeat Aristocrow's master, the steam-powered Steam Smythe, if he is to save his cousin's farm!

added.title: Super-Villain Team-Up
added.description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

added.title: Scared Silly
added.description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: The Unnaturals
added.description: Ben learns that evil robots have replaced all the kids at the Little League World Series. And now they want to replace the President of the USA!

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
added.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Dynamic Du-Oh-No
added.description: When Snowy and Jestah team up to execute a mysterious plan involving rare freeze-berries, Batwing and Buff pair up to take on the dastardly duo, but Batwing decides to carry out the mission herself, putting both her and Buff at risk.

added.title: To the Batmobile!
added.description: When all of the Batwheels (except for Bam) mysteriously disappear, Bam enlists the help of A.D.A.M, the original Batmobile, to help save his friends. Along the way, Bam comes to appreciate the old-school mobile's different crimefighting style as they team up to take on the Legion of Zoom.

added.title: Taz Recycle
added.description: When The Looney Builders build Taz a wrecking ball vehicle, he struggles to learn how to operate it.

added.title: Party Boat
added.description: The Looney Builders build a party boat for Mac and Tosh when Tweety accidentally makes a mistake but doesn't ask for help.

added.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
added.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

added.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
added.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

added.title: Dia de los Muertos
added.description: Blippi wonders how do you celebrate Dia De Los Muertos?

added.title: Scare Contest
added.description: Blippi wonders is it really fun to be scared?

added.title: Trick or Treat
added.description: D.BO wonders what is trick-or-treating?

added.title: Halloween Song
added.description: A special animated music video episode to the tune of Blippi's new "Halloween Song"

added.title: Halloween Party
added.description: D.BO wonders how do you throw the best Halloween party ever?

added.title: Trick or Treat
added.description: Mei, Mummy and Ella (3 generations of the same family) are all trick or treating together around the CITY!

added.title: Do the Skeleton Dance - Halloween Special
added.description: Lellobee City Farm learns to do the groovy Skeleton Dance for Halloween.

added.title: Wheels on the Bus
added.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

added.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
added.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

added.title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
added.description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!
